Summer Fridays are over, so to mourn its passing the office cool kids headed out to lunch! With trepidation we randomly picked the nearly empty Bistango, but we must have started a trend because people began started pouring in after us. We marveled at the affordable lunch menu... $5 salads and less than $10 entrees galore! I ordered the Baked Lasagna with Mixed Vegetables ($7) and received a large cheesy square of ricotta and pasta drowning in marinara, topped with not over cooked zucchini and carrots, and under a substantially heavy melted blanket of mozzarella. The atmosphere was nondescript except for the creepy photoshop-polarized canvas prints of the same girl over and over all over the walls...
